HEADWORD: Armageddon
<hw>Ar`ma*ged"don</hw> <pr>(⟦aum⟧r*m⟦adot⟧"j⟦ecr⟧"d'n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>the final, decisive battle between the forces of good
and evil, as foretold in the Apocolypse of Saint John. Also, the site of
that battle. Used metaphorically for a vast and decisive conflict,
attended by cataclysmic destruction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

